{"id":"gsc-uy2","title":"Persist plan data on keyboard interrupt and unhandled exceptions","description":"Currently, plan data (commits, result_store, context) is only persisted to the temp directory on successful completion. If the user hits Ctrl-C or an unhandled exception occurs mid-run, all the LLM's work is lost — the emitted commits, investigation results, and partial plans vanish.

Since agentic runs can be expensive (30-50k+ tokens), losing that work is painful. The plan persistence code already exists (writes to gsc-plan-* temp dirs); it just needs to run on abnormal exit too.

Fix: Add signal handler for SIGINT and wrap the agentic loop in try/finally (or atexit) to call the plan persistence logic. Should persist whatever state exists at interruption time — partial commits, result_store, conversation history. The temp directory path should still be printed to stderr so the user can find it.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"el-github@elangley.org","created_at":"2026-03-01T19:05:05Z","created_by":"Edward Langley","updated_at":"2026-03-01T19:05:05Z"}

{"id":"gsc-4f7","title":"Non-ASCII filenames in hunk IDs cause finalize_commits to fail","description":"When a file has a non-ASCII or special-character name (e.g. a Nix build log named 'Symbol\342\200\231s function definition is void: $buff'), its hunk ID contains octal-escaped bytes. When emit_commit formats the remaining-hunk list as a markdown backtick span, the backslashes get double-escaped (\342 → \\342). The LLM then submits the double-escaped form to finalize_commits, which can't match it against the stored ID, so validation fails. On the last turn this surfaces as a cryptic RuntimeError rather than a clean error.

Confirmed from result_store: r39 shows the ID rendered with single-backslash octal escaping in the list; r67 shows finalize_commits rejecting the double-backslash form the LLM submitted.

Fix: sanitize hunk IDs at creation time — replace non-ASCII bytes with safe ASCII (percent-encode or strip them) so the round-trip through markdown formatting is lossless. Note: gsc-h63 (use content hashes for hunk IDs) would also eliminate this class of bug.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"el-github@elangley.org","created_at":"2026-03-07T08:17:49Z","created_by":"Edward Langley","updated_at":"2026-03-07T08:17:49Z"}

{"id":"gsc-01b","title":"read_file serves binary content instead of rejecting it","description":"The read_file tool does not detect binary files. When the LLM calls read_file on a binary file (e.g. files.db-shm — a SQLite WAL shared-memory file), 32KB of binary garbage is returned, stored in result_store, and consumed from the context budget without providing any useful information.

Confirmed from result_store r64: raw binary bytes stored as a string.

Fix: after reading file content, check for null bytes or failed UTF-8 decode and return a short descriptive message like '[binary file — N bytes, cannot display]' instead of the raw bytes. The existing is_binary flag on DiffHunk shows the concept already exists for diff hunks; apply the same detection to read_file.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"el-github@elangley.org","created_at":"2026-03-07T08:19:04Z","created_by":"Edward Langley","updated_at":"2026-03-07T08:19:04Z"}

{"id":"gsc-jf1","title":"finalize_commits validation failure on last turn raises cryptic RuntimeError","description":"When finalize_commits is called on the final turn but its validation fails (e.g. unknown hunk IDs in skipped_hunks), the LLM has no remaining turns to retry. The agentic loop then raises RuntimeError('agentic_loop exceeded N turns without calling finalize_commits') even though finalize_commits was called — it just failed. The error message is misleading and the partial plan (which may contain good emitted commits) is surfaced only via the interrupt handler.

Confirmed: turn 30/30 was finalize_commits, r67 shows the validation error, the RuntimeError was still raised.

Fix options: (1) treat a failed finalize_commits call on the last turn as a terminal error and surface the partial plan with a clear message; (2) give the LLM one extra turn when finalize_commits fails validation on the last turn; (3) on turn-limit exhaustion, attempt to auto-finalize with all remaining unassigned hunks moved to skipped_hunks.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"el-github@elangley.org","created_at":"2026-03-07T08:19:04Z","created_by":"Edward Langley","updated_at":"2026-03-07T08:19:04Z"}

{"id":"gsc-jf1","title":"finalize_commits validation failure on last turn raises cryptic RuntimeError","description":"When finalize_commits is called on the final turn but its validation fails (e.g. unknown hunk IDs in skipped_hunks), the LLM has no remaining turns to retry. The agentic loop then raises RuntimeError('agentic_loop exceeded N turns without calling finalize_commits') even though finalize_commits was called — it just failed. The error message is misleading and the partial plan (which may contain good emitted commits) is surfaced only via the interrupt handler.

Confirmed: turn 30/30 was finalize_commits, r67 shows the validation error, the RuntimeError was still raised.

Fix options: (1) treat a failed finalize_commits call on the last turn as a terminal error and surface the partial plan with a clear message; (2) give the LLM one extra turn when finalize_commits fails validation on the last turn; (3) on turn-limit exhaustion, attempt to auto-finalize with all remaining unassigned hunks moved to skipped_hunks.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"el-github@elangley.org","created_at":"2026-03-07T08:19:04Z","created_by":"Edward Langley","updated_at":"2026-03-07T08:22:37Z","closed_at":"2026-03-07T08:22:37Z","close_reason":"Implemented in 8bd153a"}

{"id":"gsc-6dz","title":"LLM front-loads all investigation before emitting; prompt should encourage emit-as-you-go","description":"In practice the LLM reads many files exhaustively before calling emit_commit even once. In the observed 26-hunk run, 9 turns were spent on read_file/get_diff calls before the first emit_commit attempt (turn 15), leaving only 15 turns for 9 planned commits plus finalize — not enough. This pattern reliably exhausts the turn budget for repos with many new untracked files.

The AGENTIC_SYSTEM_PROMPT says 'You do NOT need to emit immediately — investigate first to build a holistic picture' which actively encourages this front-loading.

Fix: revise the prompt to encourage emitting commits progressively as each logical group becomes clear, reserving investigation calls only for genuinely ambiguous hunks. Something like: 'Emit each commit as soon as you have enough information for that logical group — do not wait until you have investigated all files.'","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"el-github@elangley.org","created_at":"2026-03-07T08:19:04Z","created_by":"Edward Langley","updated_at":"2026-03-07T08:19:04Z"}
